{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "package.json",
      "version": "0.7.1"
    }
  ],
  "text": "In a security audit of the Node.js web stack, I identified all package.json files declaring cookie as a direct runtime dependency across the four evaluated repositories. Only sg-evals/expressjs-express (version 4.21.1) declares the cookie package as a runtime dependency, with version constraint 0.7.1 specified in its package.json file at the repository root. The other repositories (sg-evals/lodash, sg-evals/nodejs-node, and sg-evals/prisma-prisma) do not declare cookie as a direct runtime dependency. Note that version 0.7.1 is not vulnerable to CVE-2024-47764, which affects versions prior to 0.7.0."
}

